<p>
Jobs View is a dedicated window that presents sync activity with chunk-level
visibility so operators can monitor progress in real time. It is intended to
make run state easier to interpret during active processing and follow-up
analysis.
</p>

<p>
This page is placeholder content and will be expanded with detailed guidance on
navigation, status interpretation, and expected behavior as jobs move through
queued, active, and completed stages.
</p>

<p>
Chunking in Jobs View is designed to expose how work is divided and processed
throughout a sync run. This helps teams understand throughput, locate stalled
work segments, and verify whether a run completed as expected.
</p>

<p>
Additional detail will be added with screenshots and field-by-field definitions
for chunk progress, timing, completion summaries, and any failure or retry
signals shown in the window.
</p>
